===Etymology===
Perhaps {{der|zh|sit}}: {{cog|cdm|||tr=tuŋʔ-|to plant}}, {{m|cdm|दुङ्‌||tr=duŋ|shoot; sprout}}, {{m|cdm|दुङ्‌सा||tr=duŋ-|to sprout; to grow}}. Compare {{och-l|腫|to swell}} and {{och-l|踵|heel}}.

Related to {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*k-coːŋʔ||seed}} ({{cog|vi|giống||seed}}), which is likely a loanword from Chinese ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1948}}).

Pronunciation 2 ({{m-g|to sow; to plant}}) is the exoactive derivation of pronunciation 1 ({{m-g|seed}}) formed with the Old Chinese suffix [[Reconstruction:Old Chinese/-s|*-s]].

